Vs, installation of driver fatigue; monitoring systems, automated door closure and GPS for speed monitoring. Enforced safe tarpaulin removal process and; developed model loading sites inside premises in Supply Chain Division. Ensured safe Forklift operations by fixing 360-; degree camera, proximity sensors to increase operator situational awareness of forklift operators.; Preparing accident investigations report for any such kind of incident and accidents inside & outside factory premises and; natural deaths during transportation on road, successfully finding out root causes, system deficiencies & human factors; during investigation.; Successfully established a system of training, validation & certification system for LMVs, Forklifts & heavy vehicles before; gate pass generation.; Established daily management activities of shift safety operations & shift safety inspectors for 24/7 manning of safety; control room.; Reinforced the Contractor management system in MEL finding high risk contractors in every department for site severity; audits and third-party star rating system.; Developed an online safety observation record as management system to ensure and immediate action on high-risk; severity four & five observations. Online logging helps to find safety champions according to their involvement in job.; Developed safety modules for employees and staff safety skill and knowledge development to demonstrate safety; leadership at workplace.; Safety performance added in yearly appraisals of every member of staff for more proactive towards safety.; Involved Pre-Commissioning, Commissioning & operation of thermal power plant operation in MEL. Prepared JSA and; inspection during the activities; Prepare safety committee for discussion on safety related issues and its development way forward.; Conducting various weekly HSE review Meeting, statuary meeting, MOM and KOM with all statutory bodies and; stakeholders.; Implementation of various safety standard in project site during the project work at M/s SIL, M/s PCEPL and M/s tkIS; such as color coding for tools, tackles and equipment, Procedure development, Review and approval of procedure, site; safety audit, safety walkthrough, Heavy lifting and rigging and report making etc.; ROLES & RESPONSIBILITY; Handholding contractors to develop model working places & skill development of workforce and ensure that they are; complying with M/s tkIS Safety standards.; Enforcing M/s tkIS No mobile use & alcohol use prevention policy at workplace & on road.; Motivating contractor site safety supervisors to submit more near miss and report unsafe actions & unsafe conditions at; workplaces for safety compliance.; Managing off roll safety officers, manning & deployment to different sites for active monitoring & inspections. Sending; daily MIS reports to HODs and HO.; Attending department daily meeting to update on safety issues & actions required from line manager. As per monthly; charter conducting different type of safety audits in department. Conducting mass communication meetings at different; sites to promote safety culture.; Preparing various mass mailers on road safety, the Importance of logging near miss to all employees as part of a safety; communication.; Apex Sub committees on project to develop Annual target and objective Plan strategies for projects. In the committee; also raising critical concerns & gaps for taking action by concerned person.; Conducting Job Safety Analysis, HIRA of all jobs to ensure activities as per SOP & implementation control measures during; the job.; Review of procedure and SOP for further significant improvement and action.; Imparting training on HIRA, JSA and job specific and past accidents lesson to developing safe perception on related; activities.; Regularly conducting safety inspection and audits, highlight severity four & five observations, informing RCM and line; manager for correction the same.; Arranging visit to third parties, contractor, and Subcommittee 